<section id="firefox_addons">
<title>Enable add-ons</title>

<para>
In <application>Firefox</application> under <guimenuitem>Tools</guimenuitem> select <guilabel>Add-ons</guilabel>
and enable the plugins. 
Note that this must be done individually for each user.
</para>

</section>

<!-- ============================================================ -->

<section id="firefox_browser_info">
<title>Check out browser info</title>

<para>
See what <application>Firefox</application> thinks about itself:
Type <systemitem>about:</systemitem> in the <guilabel>address bar</guilabel>,
and try
<itemizedlist>
	<listitem><para>
		<systemitem>about:support</systemitem> for some system information
	</para></listitem><listitem><para>
		<systemitem>about:plugins</systemitem> to see what plugins we have
	</para></listitem><listitem><para>
		<systemitem>about:robots</systemitem> (-:
	</para></listitem><listitem><para>
		<systemitem>about:about</systemitem> to list them all
	</para></listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</para>

<para>
And see what the rest of the world think about your <application>Firefox</application>:
<itemizedlist>
	<listitem><para>
		<ulink url="http://useragentstring.com/">useragentstring.com</ulink>
	</para></listitem><listitem><para>
		<ulink url="http://panopticlick.eff.org/">panopticlick.eff.org</ulink>
	</para></listitem><listitem><para>
		<ulink url="http://browserspy.dk/browser.php/">browserspy.dk</ulink>
	</para></listitem><listitem><para>
